## DESIGN NOTES
================================================================================

- Recovery scenes are now consistently normalized to include `scene`, `body`,
  `options`, `meta`, and `metadata` keys at root level
- Recovery metadata is propagated from nested `narrative.*` wrapper to root
- `_is_strong_scene()` prevents weak scenes from overwriting last-good anchors
- Policy escalation kicks in after 3+ consecutive failures on same anchor
- All recovery scenes carry `meta.recovered=true` for easy identification
- Recovery count is tracked per-scene via `recovery_count_by_scene` dict
- MAX_RECOVERIES=50 cap prevents unbounded history growth